      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_question_banks" data-step-uuid="37A266C2-115B-4F2B-812F-42ACACC9CFA5">
    <h2 id="open_question_banks" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open Question Banks</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/766/686/original/d5a00c42-4b1c-46a4-86de-ae787ce06828.png" srcset="" alt="Open Question Banks" height="304" width="174">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_A49CFBB0-1E13-0135-862C-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Account-level question banks are question banks created and stored at the account level. This allows users to access and use general content for quizzes.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="when_would_i_use_account_level_question_banks" data-step-uuid="EE55EC3C-B3D0-4BCF-900D-F979548B4FF8">
    <h2 id="when_would_i_use_account_level_question_banks" class="step-title screensteps-heading">When Would I Use Account-Level Question Banks?</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/766/688/original/5b9163f0-b007-4b58-adb5-c6da2c24ff37.png" srcset="" alt="When Would I Use Account-Level Question Banks?" height="425" width="693">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_A49D3670-1E13-0135-862E-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Account-level questions banks can be used to create institutional or departmental question repositories. For example, if the English department offers several courses to teach basic grammar rules to students, the department can create a sub-account level question bank. Instructors can then access the question banks to offer the same evaluation to students in different courses.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
